(130, 'The Book of Henry', '', '2017-06-16', 105, 7.4, 'Naomi Watts stars as Susan, a single mother of two, working as a waitress in a small town. Her son, Henry, is an 11-year-old genius who not only manages the family finances but acts as emotional support for his mother and younger brother. When Henry discovers that the girl next door has a terrible secret, he implores Susan to take matters into her own hands in this imaginative and emotional drama.', ' ', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w185_and_h278_bestv2/suLFg4UjvM5BoDipg2Wu3gZ802T.jpg', 382614),
(131, 'The Glass Castle', '', '2017-08-10', 127, 6.7, 'A young girl is raised in a dysfunctional family constantly on the run from the FBI. Living in poverty, she comes of age guided by her drunkard, ingenious father who distracts her with magical stories to keep her mind off the family''s dire state, and her selfish, nonconformist mother who has no intention of raising a family, along with her younger brother and sister, and her other older sister. Together, they fend for each other as they mature in an unorthodox journey that is their family life.', ' ', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w185_and_h278_bestv2/8NPP7mliHLlVMHce8SjApiRxgzm.jpg', 336000),
