(229, 'The Chinese Exclusion Act', '', '2017-12-07', 161, 0, 'For the first century of its existence, the United States had no legal restrictions on immigration. This all changed in the latter part of the 1800s, when anti-Chinese agitation by politicians, industrialists, laborers, and media led to federal laws targeting Chinese abroad and those already in the country. But THE CHINESE EXCLUSION ACT goes far beyond the legislation of its title with a sweeping chronicle of the entire exclusion era: the survival and growth of Chinese American communities in the face of prejudice and outright violence; the â€œpaperâ€� sons and daughters who emigrated despite the seemingly impassable barriers; and the legal challenges that produced some of the most momentous decisions in Supreme Court history.', ' ', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w185_and_h278_bestv2/rQSWzE4ZL5dr2KaODsGEIwLUaty.jpg', 484615),
(230, 'Santa Claus: The Movie', '', '1985-10-29', 108, 6, 'The first half of this film, set hundreds of years ago, shows how the old man who eventually became Santa Claus was given immortality and chosen to deliver toys to all the children of the world. The second half moves into the modern era, in which Patch, the head elf, strikes out on his own and falls in with an evil toy manufacturer who wants to corner the market and eliminate Santa Claus.', ' ', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w185_and_h278_bestv2/tZvGQF2623FD0MZgvOy18J5d7x5.jpg', 13764),
(231, 'Beach Rats', '', '2017-08-25', 95, 6.8, 'An aimless teenager on the outer edges of Brooklyn struggles to escape his bleak home life and navigate questions of self-identity, as he balances his time between his delinquent friends, a potential new girlfriend, and older men he meets online.', ' ', 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w185_and_h278_bestv2/oQZPPsvoipd38jasPhvJOpajbug.jpg', 426238),
